VMusic recital
p3
sVnews
p4
VThe 72nd monthly music festival, organised by the Tiruchi Tamil Isai Sangam, featured the vocal concerts of N. Rajeswari and N. Meenakshi, at the Tiruchi Tamil Sangam Hall, in the city recently.The duo was ably accompanied by Tiruvarangam Lakshminarayanan on the violin, Tiruchi V. Swaminathan on the mridangam, Anthanallur Ranganathan on the ghatam and Tiruchi Sekar on the ganjira.For peace and tranquilityK. Balamurugan, regional passport officer, who was the chief guest, said that music alone, which transcends religious and linguistic barriers, can provide solace to the people in the current scenario. Music provides peace and tranquillity and also streamlines the lifestyle of the common people.Balamurugan commended the Tiruchi Tamil Isai Sangam for doing yeoman service for the promotion of Tamil music by regularly organising music concerts. L.N. Lakshmanan, president, Tiruchi Tamil Isai Sangam, presided. K. Rangarajan, secretary and N. Mohan, vice president, offered felicitations.
